"Champier D., Bedecarrats J.P., Rivaletto M., Strub F.","Thermoelectric power generation from biomass cook stoves",2010,"Energy","35","2",,"935","942",,,10.1016/j.energy.2009.07.015,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-76549116136&partnerID=40&md5=e9918bade8e106038a756c467a8dd1c9","Innov'Adour, Direction de la Recherche et de la Valorisation, Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, avenue de l'Université, 64012 Pau Cedex, France; Laboratoire de Génie Electrique (LGE), Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, UFR Sciences et Techniques, Avenue de l'Université, 64013 Pau Cédex, France; Laboratoire de Thermique Energétique et Procédés (LaTEP), Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, UFR Sciences et Techniques, Avenue de l'Université, 64013 PAU Cédex, France; Association Planète Bois, Technopôle Hélioparc, 2 avenue Pierre Angot, 64053 Pau cedex 9, France","Champier, D., Innov'Adour, Direction de la Recherche et de la Valorisation, Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, avenue de l'Université, 64012 Pau Cedex, France, Laboratoire de Génie Electrique (LGE), Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, UFR Sciences et Techniques, Avenue de l'Université, 64013 Pau Cédex, France; Bedecarrats, J.P., Laboratoire de Thermique Energétique et Procédés (LaTEP), Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, UFR Sciences et Techniques, Avenue de l'Université, 64013 PAU Cédex, France; Rivaletto, M., Innov'Adour, Direction de la Recherche et de la Valorisation, Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, avenue de l'Université, 64012 Pau Cedex, France, Laboratoire de Génie Electrique (LGE), Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, UFR Sciences et Techniques, Avenue de l'Université, 64013 Pau Cédex, France; Strub, F., Association Planète Bois, Technopôle Hélioparc, 2 avenue Pierre Angot, 64053 Pau cedex 9, France","The use of biomass cook stoves is widespread in the rural communities of developing countries. It is important to improve the efficiency of these stoves in order to reduce the global warming contribution. An improved biomass fired stove has been developed in our laboratory and a prototype has been built. The combustion chamber is designed to achieve the almost complete combustion of wood thus increasing the efficiency and decreasing indoor air pollution. An additional development, introduced in this paper, involves the use of a thermoelectric (TE) module in order to generate electricity to power the fan and give light. The air blowing through the stove increases the air/fuel ratio to achieve a complete combustion. In the first part, the paper presents the results from an experimental benchtest using commercial TE modules (Bismuth Telluride). The evaluation of the conversion efficiency is allowed at various temperature ranges. Then, the feasibility of adding commercial TE modules to the biomass cook stove prototype is investigated searching the best position of the modules. Lastly, a TE power generator experimental set up is presented showing that a 6 watts ready to use electrical production is possible with the biomass cook stove. © 2009 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Biomass stove; Module; Seebeck cells; TE module; Thermal Energy; Thermoelectric power generator; Thermoelectricity","Biomass stove; Module; Seebeck; Seebeck cells; Thermoelectric power generators; Air quality; Biomass; Bismuth; Combustion; Combustion chambers; Conversion efficiency; Developing countries; Electric generators; Electric power generation; Global warming; Indoor air pollution; Smoke; Thermoelectric power; Stoves; atmospheric pollution; biomass; combustion; electricity generation; energy efficiency; experimental study; indoor air; temperature effect; thermal power",,,,,,"Anozie, A.N., Bakare, A.R., Sonibare, J.A., Oyebisi, T.O., Evaluation of cooking energy cost, efficiency, impact on air pollution and policy in Nigeria (2007) Energy, 32, pp. 1283-1290; Parikh, J., Balakrishnan, K., Laxmi, V., Biswas, H., Exposure from cooking with biofuels: pollution monitoring and analysis for rural Tamil Nadu, India (2001) Energy, 26, pp. 949-962; Bhattacharya, S.C., Albina, D.O., Khaing, A.M., Effects of selected parameters on performance and emission of biomass-fired cookstoves (2002) Biomass & Bioenergy, 23, pp. 387-395; Granderson, J., Sandhu, J.S., Vasquez, D., Ramirez, E., Smith, K.R., Fuel use and design analysis of improved woodburning cookstoves in the Guatemalan Highlands (2009) Biomass & Bioenergy, 33, pp. 306-315; Rowe, D.M., Thermoelectric waste heat recovery as a renewable energy source (2006) International Journal of Innovations in Energy Systems and Power, 1 (1); Nuwayhid, R.Y., Rowe, D.M., Min, G., Low cost stove-top thermoelectric generator for regions with unreliable electricity supply (2003) Renewable Energy, 28, pp. 205-222; Nuwayhid, R.Y., Shihadeh, A., Ghaddar, N., Development and testing of a domestic woodstove thermoelectric generator with natural convection cooling (2005) Energy Conversion and Management, 46, pp. 1631-1643; Lertsatitthanakorn, C., Electrical performance analysis and economic evaluation of combined biomass cook stove thermoelectric (BITE) generator (2007) Bioresource Technology, 98, pp. 1670-1674; Fairbanks JW. US Department of energy. Thermoelectrics applications reviews. In: The 5th European conference on thermoelectrics, Odessa, Ukraine; September 10-13, 2007. Available from: <http://www.ect2007.its.org/system/files/u1/pdf/10.pdf>Vining, C.Z., ∼3.5: Fifteen years of progress and things to come (2007) ECT2007, the 5th European conference on thermoelectrics, , http://www.ect2007.its.org/system/files/u1/pdf/02.pdf, Available from; Anatychuk, L.I., Current status and some prospects of thermoelectricity. Institute of Thermoelectricity (2007) Chernivtsi. Ukraine. Journal of Thermoelectricity, 2, pp. 7-20; Nuwayhid, R.Y., Hamade, R., Design and testing of a locally made loop-type thermosyphonic heat sink for stove-top thermoelectric generators (2005) Renewable Energy, 30, pp. 1101-1116; Kubo, M., Shinoda, M., Furuhata, T., Kitagawa, K., Optimization of the incision size and cold-end temperature of a thermoelectric device (2005) Energy, 30, pp. 2156-2170; Rowe, D.M., Min, G., Evaluation of thermoelectric modules for power generation (1998) Journal of Power Sources, 73, pp. 193-198; Taihuaxing thermoelectric module, power modules for converting heat sources to electricity, thermonamic electronics. Available from: www.thermonamic.com/Pspec.htmlTEG power generator & thermoelectric generator, , www.espressomilkcooler.com, Thermal Electronics Corp, Available from; Sandoz-Rosado, E., Stevens, R., Experimental characterization of thermoelectric modules and comparison with theoretical models for power generation (2009) Journal of Electronic Materials, 38 (7), pp. 1239-1244; Eakburanawat, J., Boonyaroonate, I., Development of a thermoelectric battery-charger with microcontroller-based maximum power point tracking technique (2006) Applied Energy, 83, pp. 687-704","Champier, D.; Innov'Adour, Direction de la Recherche et de la Valorisation, Université de Pau et des Pays de l'Adour, avenue de l'Université, 64012 Pau Cedex, France; email: daniel.champier@univ-pau.fr",,,,,,,,03605442,,ENEYD,,"English","Energy",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-76549116136
